</A> <B>Posted by <A HREF="http://www.monkey.org/~timothy">timothy</A>  on  Monday September 25, @11:00AM</B><BR>
<FONT size=2><B>from the blue-leds-and-promises dept.</B></FONT><BR>
<a href="http://slashdot.org/articles/00/03/23/0858230.shtml">You've been hearing about it</a> (and <i>hearing</i> about it) for months -- the Linux-based gaming console in the works from a company called Indrema. Now you can ask the questions that are on your mind about it (like when it will really and truly arrive, in the hooked-up-and-running-Quake sense, say) and get answers from company founder and CEO John Gildred. (More below.)

