</A> <B>Posted by <A HREF="mailto:jellicle@inch.com">michael</A>  on  Thursday August 17, @02:37PM</B><BR>
<FONT size=2><B>from the pro-bono dept.</B></FONT><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.fgks.com">Martin Garbus</A> and <A HREF="http://eff.org">Robin Gross</A> are the attorneys defending Emmanuel Goldstein and 2600.com in the <A HREF="http://slashdot.org/search.pl?query=decss">DeCSS case</A> that just had its first decision.  Ask them whatever you'd like about the case - we'll do the usual, forward highly-moderated questions and get their answers back to you ASAP.  Note that standard, boring questions like, "Where do you go from here?  Will you appeal?" are going to be asked and answered in other news stories, probably many times over.  This is an opportunity to ask those questions that <I>won't</I> be asked in other news stories.


