</A> <B>Posted by <A HREF="http://www.monkey.org/~timothy">timothy</A>  on  Monday July 03, @11:00AM</B><BR>
<FONT size=2><B>from the drysuits-required dept.</B></FONT><BR>
A few weeks ago, you asked questions of Ryan Lackey, CTO for HavenCo, a company dedicated to providing secure off-shore data hosting from Sealand, a principality off the coast of England. Ryan has lately survived dental emergencies, the loss of a laptop (it dropped into the North Sea -- how many people can say <i>that</i>?) and other stresses, but he's followed through with some interesting answers. He even has some ideas for how you can make a lot of money, and lists the tools you need to start your own data haven. Kudos to Ryan for taking the time to answer so thoroughly.       

